Step 1 — Create a New Repository on GitHub
Step 2 — Setup Git Locally
Initialize & First Commit
Run these commands in your project folder:
echo "# learning_git" >> App.py
code .                          # Opens VS Code
git init                        # Initialize git (.git folder created)
git add .                       # Stage all files
git status                      # Check what's staged
git commit -m "Initial commit"  # Save changes


Important: Make sure your URL ends with .git — never copy a URL with # at the end!

Step 3 — Branching
Branches let you work on features without affecting the main code.

git branch                      # See all branches
git branch Priya                # Create new branch called Priya
git checkout Priya              # Switch to Priya branch


Once you push a branch, it will appear on GitHub. You can then create a Pull Request to merge it into main